<div class="comments-body">
<p>I only just discovered pbase 2 wks. ago and regardless of the fact that we discovered a yr. apart, I completely agree with both yr. positive & negative comments about the service.</p>

<p>It looks great, is realtively easy to use & has great features (esp. compared w. blogger.com--where I came from).</p>

<p>My problem (& I think you mentioned this in somewhat technical terms which I had some trouble following) is with the CSS stylesheets & textual elements.  The editing function is miserable & is unnecessarily hard to use or figure out.  They should do a better job of explaining to users how to use stylesheets AND how to edit existing stylesheets in order to personalize them for an individual member's use.  I think that their FAQs & Help info is pretty lame.</p>

<p>Here's hoping that the good stuff stays good & the bad stuff gets fixed.</p>

<p>Richard</p>
